In 2014, the US restricted the importation of elephant trophies from Zimbabwe and Tanzania.

Despite appeals from Zimbabwe that the ban be lifted as conservation in the country is reliant on the proceeds from hunting, the ban remains in place. This week, it looks like the USA will possibly extend the ban to elephants in all countries.

